1
00:00:06,505 --> 00:00:08,805
- [whooshes]
- [tires screech]

2
00:00:10,738 --> 00:00:12,905
READY OR NOT: TEXAS

3
00:00:13,738 --> 00:00:16,738
THEY'RE GOING TO HOUSTON TODAY!

4
00:00:16,805 --> 00:00:19,371
[Woo-jung] When Yung-suk came downstairs,
I mistook him for Seo-jin.

5
00:00:19,438 --> 00:00:21,771
Not because of his face
but because of the jacket.

6
00:00:21,838 --> 00:00:23,838
Hey, you're wearing the Netflix jacket.

7
00:00:23,905 --> 00:00:26,405
THE JACKET YUNG-SUK IS WEARING NOW
IS THE ONE SEO-JIN WORE YESTERDAY

8
00:00:26,471 --> 00:00:28,738
It's like I'm watching
the rise and fall of clothes.

9
00:00:28,805 --> 00:00:30,971
Seo-jin's clothes
always end up in Yung-suk's hands.

10
00:00:31,038 --> 00:00:34,171
For some reason,
whenever the shoot is almost over,

11
00:00:34,238 --> 00:00:36,538
Seo-jin's things
end up in my hands. [chuckles]

12
00:00:36,605 --> 00:00:37,771
FOR EXAMPLE: THE NETFLIX JACKET

13
00:00:37,838 --> 00:00:39,871
"Hey, take it. I won't wear it anyway."

14
00:00:39,938 --> 00:00:42,471
- He then gives me his stuff.
- [Woo-jung] You're the drain of fashion.

15
00:00:42,538 --> 00:00:45,871
- "Drain"?
- [laughing]

16
00:00:45,938 --> 00:00:48,105
- [Woo-jung] You collect everything.
- That's not true.

17
00:00:49,338 --> 00:00:50,838
I love you, Netflix.

18
00:00:51,438 --> 00:00:53,505
[Woo-jung] Let's guess
what Seo-jin will wear today.

19
00:00:53,571 --> 00:00:55,238
He said he'd dress simply.

20
00:00:55,305 --> 00:00:56,905
[Dae-ju] A pair of black slacks…

21
00:00:56,971 --> 00:00:58,205
[Woo-jung] You don't know him yet.

22
00:00:58,271 --> 00:00:59,738
- Sneakers…
- A short-sleeve crew-neck.

23
00:00:59,805 --> 00:01:02,505
- [Woo-jung] Definitely shorts and a top.
- Yes, a short-sleeve crew-neck.

24
00:01:02,571 --> 00:01:05,938
He doesn't wear shorts very often

25
00:01:06,005 --> 00:01:09,071
because he thinks his legs are skinny
and feels self-conscious about them.

26
00:01:09,138 --> 00:01:12,238
So, I predict he'll wear the Zara pants
from yesterday and a short-sleeve top.

27
00:01:12,305 --> 00:01:13,405
[all exclaim]

28
00:01:13,471 --> 00:01:15,571
POLO SHIRT AND SHORTS

29
00:01:16,138 --> 00:01:17,705
- [Yung-suk] He's wearing shorts.
- [Woo-jung] I was right, wasn't I?

30
00:01:17,771 --> 00:01:19,271
[Yung-suk] What a surprise,
Mr. Skinny Legs.

31
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:22,005
Bye, Dallas. We'll see you again.

32
00:01:23,338 --> 00:01:25,838
It's raining more heavily today, Seo-jin.

33
00:01:26,471 --> 00:01:28,705
To think I'm going to Houston.

34
00:01:29,405 --> 00:01:31,538
We're traveling south, aren't we?

35
00:01:31,605 --> 00:01:32,738
Yes.

36
00:01:32,805 --> 00:01:34,105
Houston is a coastal city.

37
00:01:34,171 --> 00:01:35,271
Does it have beaches too?

38
00:01:35,338 --> 00:01:37,005
The sea lies a bit further south.

39
00:01:37,071 --> 00:01:39,438
- There's a resort area and islands there.
- Oh!

40
00:01:39,505 --> 00:01:43,171
- You can find anything anywhere in the US.
- [laughs]

41
00:01:43,238 --> 00:01:45,105
You can find anything you need
wherever you go.

42
00:01:45,171 --> 00:01:48,738
You should run for president
since you love the US so much.

43
00:01:49,405 --> 00:01:53,371
[chuckling] You should run for office
here in Houston instead of Andong.

44
00:01:53,438 --> 00:01:57,138
The navigation is telling us
to exit the expressway in 167 miles.

45
00:01:58,005 --> 00:02:00,338
That means we have to stay
on this road for 268 kilometers.

46
00:02:00,405 --> 00:02:01,805
We can just keep on driving.

47
00:02:01,871 --> 00:02:04,205
[Yung-suk] We're staying on this road
for 268 kilometers?

48
00:02:04,271 --> 00:02:07,271
If we had a Tesla,
I could just use its autopilot feature.

49
00:02:07,338 --> 00:02:09,305
- Right?
- You totally could.

50
00:02:09,871 --> 00:02:12,438
Americans definitely could use
the self-driving feature.

51
00:02:12,505 --> 00:02:16,071
Especially those who take the expressway
to travel long distances often.

52
00:02:16,938 --> 00:02:18,771
Why did the Tesla shares drop?

53
00:02:19,271 --> 00:02:20,538
SMALL-TIME INVESTOR THINKING OUT LOUD

54
00:02:20,605 --> 00:02:22,038
I own some Tesla shares too.

55
00:02:22,105 --> 00:02:23,471
[Seo-jin] When did you buy them?

56
00:02:23,538 --> 00:02:25,705
Your losses must be huge.

57
00:02:25,771 --> 00:02:29,905
About two months ago,
Seo-jun came to see us.

58
00:02:29,971 --> 00:02:33,138
He said, "I drove Tesla
while visiting the US,

59
00:02:33,205 --> 00:02:35,638
and it was amazing."

60
00:02:35,705 --> 00:02:39,005
He then added that
he could picture Tesla's global success.

61
00:02:39,071 --> 00:02:42,771
That prompted Yung-suk and me
to buy Tesla stock.

62
00:02:42,838 --> 00:02:44,038
- That's how it happened?
- Yes.

63
00:02:44,105 --> 00:02:46,538
Anything looks reliable
when Seo-jun recommends it.

64
00:02:46,605 --> 00:02:49,871
I guess that's why advertisers want him
to model for their products. [laughs]

65
00:02:49,938 --> 00:02:51,105
CLASSIC CASE OF JUMPING ON THE BANDWAGON

66
00:02:51,171 --> 00:02:53,738
He only said,
"I think Tesla's pretty good."

67
00:02:53,805 --> 00:02:55,405
So, we went, "Then I'm investing in it."

68
00:02:55,471 --> 00:02:58,705
AS THEY CHATTED AWAY,
THE SKY HAS GOTTEN SLIGHTLY BRIGHTER

69
00:02:58,771 --> 00:03:00,805
I'm hungry, Seo-jin.

70
00:03:00,871 --> 00:03:03,505
- [Woo-jung] I'm craving some coffee.
- Can't we get some snacks?

71
00:03:04,071 --> 00:03:06,671
[Dae-ju] There should be
a Buc-ee's ahead of us.

72
00:03:06,738 --> 00:03:08,205
Is that it?

73
00:03:08,738 --> 00:03:10,471
Is it where the raccoon sign is?
Maybe not.

74
00:03:10,538 --> 00:03:12,005
[Woo-jung] Isn't that
a squirrel or a beaver?

75
00:03:12,071 --> 00:03:13,005
REST STOP SIGN SPOTTED!

76
00:03:13,805 --> 00:03:16,405
[Seo-jin] Let's get some snacks,
finish them here, and ride on.

77
00:03:16,471 --> 00:03:18,271
BUC-EE'S IS A TEXAN MEGA REST STOP CHAIN
WITH A BEAVER MASCOT

78
00:03:18,338 --> 00:03:21,338
I wish we could eat
at a place with a stunning view.

79
00:03:21,405 --> 00:03:23,005
We've got a fine view here.

80
00:03:23,938 --> 00:03:25,105
Isn't it just fine?

81
00:03:25,171 --> 00:03:26,438
QUICK SNACK IN THE PARKING LOT!

82
00:03:26,505 --> 00:03:27,638
[Woo-jung] It's nice here.

83
00:03:27,705 --> 00:03:29,905
We bought some snacks.

84
00:03:30,538 --> 00:03:31,605
NOM

85
00:03:31,671 --> 00:03:34,171
SEO-JIN GOT A BACON, EGG, AND CHEESE TACO

86
00:03:34,238 --> 00:03:37,271
YUNG-SUK GOT A CROISSANT SANDWICH

87
00:03:37,838 --> 00:03:40,038
[Dae-ju] It feels like
we're on a trip. I like it.

88
00:03:40,105 --> 00:03:42,538
- We are on a trip.
- [Dae-ju] Are we?

89
00:03:42,605 --> 00:03:44,371
THIS IS A VARIETY SHOW
COVERING SEO-JIN'S TEXAS TRIP

90
00:03:44,438 --> 00:03:45,838
Right, we're on a trip.

91
00:03:46,338 --> 00:03:48,105
[Yung-suk] Our dad here
is on the strict side…

92
00:03:48,171 --> 00:03:49,638
LEE SEO-JIN, FATHER

93
00:03:49,705 --> 00:03:51,038
…but he handles all the driving.

94
00:03:52,671 --> 00:03:54,105
MESSY EATER

95
00:03:54,171 --> 00:03:55,438
TROUBLESOME SON DROPPED A CRUMB ALREADY

96
00:03:55,505 --> 00:03:56,571
I can't believe this.

97
00:03:56,638 --> 00:04:00,005
Hey, a crumb fell
between the car seat covers.

98
00:04:00,071 --> 00:04:00,905
No, it didn't.

99
00:04:00,971 --> 00:04:03,705
I saw it get in there.
A huge chunk just fell into the gap.

100
00:04:03,771 --> 00:04:06,871
Shoot, you're getting the food
onto my hands now. [groans]

101
00:04:06,938 --> 00:04:07,771
DISGUSTED

102
00:04:07,838 --> 00:04:11,571
I can't enjoy the sandwich
because you keep pressuring me to be neat.

103
00:04:11,638 --> 00:04:12,571
FATHER-SON CONFLICT INTENSIFIES

104
00:04:12,638 --> 00:04:14,405
- Seriously, dude.
- You got it all over there.

105
00:04:14,471 --> 00:04:16,938
- Can't you lower the window?
- [Yung-suk] What for?

106
00:04:17,005 --> 00:04:18,971
So you can let the crumbs fall outside.

107
00:04:19,538 --> 00:04:20,571
How do I open this?

108
00:04:20,638 --> 00:04:22,038
WINDOW ROLLING DOWN

109
00:04:23,038 --> 00:04:24,105
Better yet, open the door.

110
00:04:24,171 --> 00:04:25,271
GETTING TABLE-MANNER LESSONS AT 50

111
00:04:26,071 --> 00:04:28,271
- [Dae-ju] That's your favorite, isn't it?
- What do you mean?

112
00:04:28,338 --> 00:04:29,571
The long snack.

113
00:04:29,638 --> 00:04:32,638
It somehow tastes better
when you eat it at a rest stop.

114
00:04:32,705 --> 00:04:34,138
SEO-JIN'S REST STOP FAVORITE, JERKY

115
00:04:34,205 --> 00:04:35,971
[Dae-ju] It's jerky.

116
00:04:36,038 --> 00:04:39,105
It's the jerky Seo-jin always buys
whenever he needs to drive.

117
00:04:39,171 --> 00:04:40,738
It's got six grams of protein.

118
00:04:41,471 --> 00:04:43,838
"Macho Man" Randy Savage
used to model for this brand.

119
00:04:43,905 --> 00:04:46,871
FORMER WRESTLER RANDY SAVAGE WAS PERFECT
FOR THE SNACK BRAND WITH A WILD IMAGE

120
00:04:46,938 --> 00:04:49,205
It looks like you're using
a traditional tobacco pipe.

121
00:04:49,271 --> 00:04:52,171
It reminds me of the <i>gombangdae.</i>

122
00:04:52,238 --> 00:04:54,338
Should I hold one of those
and sing a folk tune?

123
00:04:54,405 --> 00:04:55,871
SHORT BUT "TASTEFUL" BREAK WITH THE JERKY

124
00:04:56,438 --> 00:04:59,038
BACK ON THE ROAD TO HOUSTON

125
00:04:59,105 --> 00:05:01,671
Can you pass me the glasses
in my bag, Woo-jung?

126
00:05:01,738 --> 00:05:04,405
- [gasps] Isn't this so pretty?
- My goodness.

127
00:05:04,471 --> 00:05:06,071
Your glasses case is gorgeous.

128
00:05:06,138 --> 00:05:07,938
He gets bored with little items like this

129
00:05:08,005 --> 00:05:09,971
and hands them over
to crew members soon enough.

130
00:05:10,038 --> 00:05:11,905
Stick around and collect it.

131
00:05:11,971 --> 00:05:13,305
Spoken like the drain of fashion. [laughs]

132
00:05:13,371 --> 00:05:15,705
THE TAP NOW HAS HIS GLASSES

133
00:05:15,771 --> 00:05:19,238
[Yung-suk] But everything
is bound to end up going down the drain.

134
00:05:19,305 --> 00:05:20,305
[all laughing]

135
00:05:20,371 --> 00:05:22,371
WATER ALWAYS GATHERS AT THE DRAIN

136
00:05:22,438 --> 00:05:24,938
Do you want the shoes I'm wearing now?

137
00:05:25,471 --> 00:05:26,905
- Sure.
- I will when we're back home.

138
00:05:26,971 --> 00:05:29,905
Okay, hand it over.
You can give them to me without asking.

139
00:05:29,971 --> 00:05:31,805
Do I see Houston up ahead?

140
00:05:31,871 --> 00:05:33,871
[Yung-suk] Looks like it.
What's with the thick fog, though?

141
00:05:33,938 --> 00:05:35,471
HOUSTON'S SKYSCRAPERS FILL THE HORIZON

142
00:05:36,038 --> 00:05:38,538
[Woo-jung] Hey,
the skyscrapers to our left are…

143
00:05:38,605 --> 00:05:40,405
[soft rock music plays]

144
00:05:40,471 --> 00:05:44,305
CITY OF ENERGY AND SPACE, HOUSTON

145
00:05:44,938 --> 00:05:48,205
FIRST ENERGY, PETROLEUM

146
00:05:48,271 --> 00:05:51,738
WORLD'S HIGHEST CONCENTRATION
OF ENERGY COMPANIES

147
00:05:51,805 --> 00:05:57,605
ANOTHER ENERGY SOURCE
HEATING UP THE CITY IS SPORTS

148
00:05:57,671 --> 00:06:01,971
HOME OF HOUSTON ROCKETS, HOUSTON ASTROS,
HOUSTON TEXANS, AND MANY MORE FAMOUS TEAMS

149
00:06:02,038 --> 00:06:04,338
LAST BUT NOT LEAST, HOUSTON'S PRIDE

150
00:06:07,205 --> 00:06:12,071
LET'S VISIT HOUSTON,
THE SECOND CITY ON THE TRIP

151
00:06:12,138 --> 00:06:15,871
The actual launch site is in Florida.

152
00:06:16,538 --> 00:06:18,071
There's just a research facility here?

153
00:06:18,138 --> 00:06:20,371
Yes, there's also the control center.

154
00:06:21,138 --> 00:06:25,138
Space Shuttle Discovery
was last launched in 2011.

155
00:06:25,205 --> 00:06:27,971
WITH 39 FLIGHTS,
DISCOVERY CARRIED OUT THE MOST MISSIONS

156
00:06:28,038 --> 00:06:31,005
That launch was its 39th flight.

157
00:06:31,071 --> 00:06:32,738
It stayed in service for a long time.

158
00:06:33,405 --> 00:06:35,305
Did they not launch anything recently?

159
00:06:36,438 --> 00:06:39,105
It's no longer such a big deal these days.

160
00:06:39,905 --> 00:06:43,205
[Yung-suk] Space travel's lost
its novelty, it's become of a money pit.

161
00:06:43,271 --> 00:06:49,171
Do you remember Jonny Kim,
the Korean-American astronaut?

162
00:06:49,671 --> 00:06:53,438
I hear he's set to go to space
on a Russian spacecraft.

163
00:06:54,005 --> 00:06:57,405
Can you guess how Namuwiki
summarizes Jonny Kim's bio?

164
00:06:57,471 --> 00:07:02,471
"An American NASA astronaut,
naval aviator, surgeon,

165
00:07:02,538 --> 00:07:05,838
lieutenant commander of the US Navy,
and Navy SEAL."

166
00:07:06,405 --> 00:07:09,438
- He's got the brains and brawn.
- [Yung-suk] Yes, he's the total package.

167
00:07:09,505 --> 00:07:11,805
How can one man have it all?

168
00:07:11,871 --> 00:07:13,171
PRIME EXAMPLE OF THE PERFECT MAN

169
00:07:13,238 --> 00:07:14,305
Tell me about it.

170
00:07:14,805 --> 00:07:17,405
He must have a fault of some sort.

171
00:07:17,471 --> 00:07:20,638
Maybe he's a messy eater.
He might drop crumbs.

172
00:07:20,705 --> 00:07:21,805
CONNECTING JONNY KIM TO YUNG-SUK

173
00:07:22,871 --> 00:07:23,771
Hey, it says NASA.

174
00:07:23,838 --> 00:07:25,038
THEY'VE ALMOST REACHED THEIR STOP

175
00:07:25,838 --> 00:07:28,771
This area must be
what you might call a NASA town.

176
00:07:28,838 --> 00:07:31,038
- That McDonald's statue is so cute.
- That's so lovely.

177
00:07:31,105 --> 00:07:33,638
- [Woo-jung] The statue is holding fries.
- [Yung-suk] My goodness.

178
00:07:33,705 --> 00:07:35,038
[Woo-jung] That astronaut
has a pack of fries.

179
00:07:35,105 --> 00:07:36,105
EVEN ASTRONAUTS HAVE FRIES IN HOUSTON

180
00:07:36,171 --> 00:07:38,871
This looks like the entryway
to Space Center Houston.

181
00:07:38,938 --> 00:07:40,671
[Woo-jung] Oh,
Space Center Houston looks amazing.

182
00:07:40,738 --> 00:07:42,871
AFTER A LONG 4-HOUR DRIVE,
THEY GET A GLIMPSE OF THE NASA SITE

183
00:07:42,938 --> 00:07:44,638
[Dae-ju] Oh, man. NASA.
To think I'm visiting NASA.

184
00:07:45,205 --> 00:07:46,838
You can see it on the left.

185
00:07:47,805 --> 00:07:49,171
Do you think that's the real deal?

186
00:07:49,238 --> 00:07:51,671
- [Woo-jung] On top of the Boeing 747…
- [Yung-suk] Maybe it's a replica?

187
00:07:51,738 --> 00:07:54,438
[Seo-jin] It would carry the spacecraft up
and have it take off from there.

188
00:07:54,505 --> 00:07:55,438
SPACEX FALCON 9 BOOSTER

189
00:07:55,505 --> 00:07:57,238
[Yung-suk] That looks like the real deal.

190
00:07:57,305 --> 00:07:59,905
[Seo-jin] It is the real deal.
Everything here is retired machinery.

191
00:08:00,471 --> 00:08:02,471
- There are so many visitors.
- It's pretty crowded.

192
00:08:02,538 --> 00:08:04,471
It's almost like an amusement park.

193
00:08:04,538 --> 00:08:07,138
KEY FORCE BEHIND MANKIND'S LEAP INTO SPACE

194
00:08:07,205 --> 00:08:08,605
[exhilarating music plays]

195
00:08:08,671 --> 00:08:12,071
NATIONAL AERONAUTICS
AND SPACE ADMINISTRATION, NASA

196
00:08:12,638 --> 00:08:15,805
JUST LIKE A THEME PARK,
COUNTLESS TOURISTS VISIT EVERY YEAR

197
00:08:16,371 --> 00:08:19,671
THERE'S ALSO A TRAM TOUR
TAKING YOU ALL ACROSS THE NASA FACILITY

198
00:08:19,738 --> 00:08:22,605
THE KEY ATTRACTION OF HOUSTON!

199
00:08:23,671 --> 00:08:25,938
I must've made it big to visit NASA.

200
00:08:27,171 --> 00:08:28,805
It's not an easy place to visit.

201
00:08:28,871 --> 00:08:29,938
IT'S THE NASA FACILITY FROM THE TALES!

202
00:08:30,671 --> 00:08:32,005
Let's take a group photo.

203
00:08:32,071 --> 00:08:33,571
Right here.

204
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:34,471
TAKES OFF

205
00:08:34,538 --> 00:08:35,438
He's running away.

206
00:08:35,505 --> 00:08:37,105
[Yung-suk] Let's take one
together, Dae-ju.

207
00:08:37,171 --> 00:08:38,538
Join us for a photo, Seo-jin.

208
00:08:39,271 --> 00:08:41,071
JUST LIKE OUR FATHERS,
SEO-JIN AVOIDS BEING PHOTOGRAPHED

209
00:08:41,138 --> 00:08:41,971
[Ye-seul] Here we go.

210
00:08:42,038 --> 00:08:44,438
ACTUALLY, SEO-JIN HAS BEEN HERE BEFORE,
SO HE'S NOT THAT EXCITED

211
00:08:45,005 --> 00:08:46,171
Three, two, one.

212
00:08:46,238 --> 00:08:47,505
ONLY THE NEWCOMERS TAKE A PHOTO

213
00:08:48,338 --> 00:08:51,271
SOUVENIR PHOTO WITHOUT SEO-JIN

214
00:08:51,838 --> 00:08:55,005
FINALLY ENTERING THE NASA FACILITY!

215
00:09:00,471 --> 00:09:03,638
NASA'S OFFICIAL VISITOR CENTER
AND THE HUB OF EDUCATION

216
00:09:04,205 --> 00:09:08,338
OFFERS A RANGE OF HIGHLY RARE EXHIBITS

217
00:09:08,405 --> 00:09:10,705
Let's hit the gift shop first.

218
00:09:10,771 --> 00:09:13,605
- [chuckles]
- What? [in English]

219
00:09:13,671 --> 00:09:16,305
[in Korean] We're at NASA's Space Center,
and you want us to go to the gift shop?

220
00:09:16,371 --> 00:09:18,538
The way I see it,
you'd have the most fun there.

221
00:09:18,605 --> 00:09:21,005
- Aren't we going to check out Apollo 11?
- What?

222
00:09:21,071 --> 00:09:22,705
- [Yung-suk] Apollo 11…
- [Woo-jung] Are you going to skip it?

223
00:09:22,771 --> 00:09:23,605
- [Seo-jin] Skip what?
- [Yung-suk] Apollo 11.

224
00:09:23,671 --> 00:09:25,005
- [Dae-ju] It's the real thing.
- [Woo-jung] Yes, that one.

225
00:09:25,071 --> 00:09:27,038
- We're seeing it now.
- [Woo-jung] Well, yes, but…

226
00:09:27,105 --> 00:09:28,805
Shouldn't we go there first and…

227
00:09:28,871 --> 00:09:30,105
- [Woo-jung] There's a long line.
- First off…

228
00:09:30,171 --> 00:09:32,438
The line is for the VR experience.

229
00:09:32,505 --> 00:09:35,005
- [Dae-ju] Didn't you say it's amazing?
- Yes, it's amazing.

230
00:09:35,071 --> 00:09:36,238
Okay. Let's go then.

231
00:09:36,305 --> 00:09:37,371
THIS FATHER HAS A SET PLAN

232
00:09:37,438 --> 00:09:39,905
VR EXPERIENCE: COME JOIN US LATER

233
00:09:39,971 --> 00:09:42,338
I'm suggesting that we take a look here

234
00:09:42,405 --> 00:09:45,338
to get hyped up
before seeing the main exhibits.

235
00:09:45,405 --> 00:09:48,338
FIRST STOP TO GET HYPED UP

236
00:09:48,405 --> 00:09:51,538
NASA'S GIFT SHOP

237
00:09:51,605 --> 00:09:52,438
- This one?
- Yes.

238
00:09:52,505 --> 00:09:54,471
It's so cute. I want one.

239
00:09:54,538 --> 00:09:55,605
So soon?

240
00:09:55,671 --> 00:09:56,971
There are more caps over there.

241
00:09:57,038 --> 00:09:59,038
Doesn't this have a lovely retro vibe?

242
00:09:59,105 --> 00:10:00,705
But there are more further in.

243
00:10:00,771 --> 00:10:02,571
Don't get so excited.
You got worked up again.

244
00:10:02,638 --> 00:10:05,238
- I'm not getting worked up.
- Put it down and take a look first.

245
00:10:05,305 --> 00:10:06,205
TREATING HIM LIKE A 7-YEAR-OLD

246
00:10:06,271 --> 00:10:09,171
IN THE END,
THE SURPRISINGLY CHARMING MERCH

247
00:10:09,805 --> 00:10:12,038
INFATUATES YUNG-SUK

248
00:10:13,005 --> 00:10:14,605
Why is this so cheap?

249
00:10:14,671 --> 00:10:16,038
It's from Champion.

250
00:10:16,105 --> 00:10:17,505
- That's from Champion?
- Yes.

251
00:10:17,571 --> 00:10:19,605
- Oh, wow.
- [Dae-ju] It's a branded item.

252
00:10:20,638 --> 00:10:23,605
SEO-JIN QUICKLY CALLS DIBS
ON THE CHAMPION ANORAK

253
00:10:23,671 --> 00:10:25,505
This is a typical office outfit.

254
00:10:25,571 --> 00:10:28,205
- Yes, for indoors.
- It's what we'd wear in the editing room.

255
00:10:28,271 --> 00:10:31,771
Pair that with the T-shirt over there,
and you'll look like a NASA employee.

256
00:10:31,838 --> 00:10:32,671
PROUD

257
00:10:32,738 --> 00:10:34,105
But I don't want that.

258
00:10:34,171 --> 00:10:35,871
I've got a job of my own.

259
00:10:35,938 --> 00:10:37,971
Wear that underneath the hoodie.

260
00:10:38,038 --> 00:10:39,871
- Hey, it's from Champion.
- [chuckles] Yes.

261
00:10:39,938 --> 00:10:41,538
Pair those two together…

262
00:10:41,605 --> 00:10:43,171
YUNG-SUK IS PERSUADED YET AGAIN

263
00:10:43,238 --> 00:10:46,038
…and they'll probably let us in
even without the tickets.

264
00:10:46,105 --> 00:10:47,905
AKA BACKSTAGE PASS TO NASA FACILITY

265
00:10:47,971 --> 00:10:49,471
Where's Dae-ju?

266
00:10:50,038 --> 00:10:51,238
Why don't you get this hoodie?

267
00:10:51,305 --> 00:10:52,371
TIME FOR DAE-JU'S MAKEOVER

268
00:10:52,438 --> 00:10:55,338
[laughing] He must have an ensemble
in mind. Don't keep egging him on.

269
00:10:55,405 --> 00:10:56,405
Come on.

270
00:10:56,471 --> 00:10:59,938
- It's on sale.
- Dae-ju has his taste too.

271
00:11:00,005 --> 00:11:00,838
Hey, Dae-ju.

272
00:11:00,905 --> 00:11:01,805
FATHER WANTS THE BEST FOR HIS SON

273
00:11:01,871 --> 00:11:03,671
I did think this looked cute.

274
00:11:03,738 --> 00:11:05,671
Yes, this is the best by far.

275
00:11:05,738 --> 00:11:09,171
Can't you let him choose his own clothes?

276
00:11:09,238 --> 00:11:11,838
- I have similar items at home.
- You're acting like a control freak.

277
00:11:11,905 --> 00:11:14,871
- [both laugh]
- You think this suits me, right?

278
00:11:15,405 --> 00:11:18,105
- Well, yes--
- But doesn't it scream office worker?

279
00:11:18,171 --> 00:11:19,638
But you are one.

280
00:11:19,705 --> 00:11:21,705
- [laughs]
- You can actually wear it at work.

281
00:11:21,771 --> 00:11:23,571
But I don't work at NASA.

282
00:11:23,638 --> 00:11:26,905
When the weather turns chilly in spring,
you can put this on in the office.

283
00:11:26,971 --> 00:11:28,105
SWEET BUT INSISTENT

284
00:11:28,171 --> 00:11:30,871
By the way, everyone was wearing this
at the Smoothie King.

285
00:11:30,938 --> 00:11:33,238
Of course.
It's how it is in the US these days.

286
00:11:33,305 --> 00:11:34,471
- Really?
- Sure.

287
00:11:35,138 --> 00:11:36,538
CHANGED UNDER SEO-JIN'S GUIDANCE

288
00:11:36,605 --> 00:11:39,438
Doesn't it look like
I would be the best student here?

289
00:11:39,505 --> 00:11:43,605
[Ye-seul] You each look like
a NASA employee, a donor, and a geek.

290
00:11:43,671 --> 00:11:46,471
That's the vibe I'm getting.

291
00:11:46,538 --> 00:11:48,371
We can sit across from each other.

292
00:11:48,871 --> 00:11:51,738
LET'S HOP ON THE TRAM!

293
00:11:54,105 --> 00:11:55,105
Hello.

294
00:11:55,171 --> 00:11:58,105
- I'm a NASA employee.
- [chuckles]

295
00:11:58,171 --> 00:11:59,671
My name's Alex Nah.

296
00:11:59,738 --> 00:12:00,571
NASA EMPLOYEE'S VLOG

297
00:12:00,638 --> 00:12:03,471
Today, I'll show you
how my day at work goes.

298
00:12:04,038 --> 00:12:06,005
THIS GUY COULDN'T CARE LESS…

299
00:12:06,738 --> 00:12:07,671
I work at…

300
00:12:07,738 --> 00:12:09,938
I study alien parasites.

301
00:12:10,005 --> 00:12:11,338
ALEX NAH, ALIEN PARASITE EXPERT

302
00:12:11,405 --> 00:12:13,971
- Ones that infect your liver.
- That's why you're keeping worms?

303
00:12:14,038 --> 00:12:15,138
[all laugh]

304
00:12:15,205 --> 00:12:17,071
This is the parasite
I discovered recently.

305
00:12:17,905 --> 00:12:19,771
Say hello to my friends.

306
00:12:19,838 --> 00:12:21,105
Capture your stomach.

307
00:12:21,171 --> 00:12:22,438
ALIEN PARASITE INCUBATION ROOM

308
00:12:22,505 --> 00:12:24,938
- [all laugh]
- You're raising parasites in here.

309
00:12:25,005 --> 00:12:27,271
They're long gone.
They're in a better place now.

310
00:12:27,338 --> 00:12:29,238
YUNG-SUK RECENTLY TOOK AN ANTIPARASITIC

311
00:12:29,305 --> 00:12:30,438
[tour guide in English]

312
00:12:30,505 --> 00:12:31,971
Welcome to the NASA tram tour

313
00:12:32,038 --> 00:12:34,171
to the Historic Mission Control Center.

314
00:12:34,238 --> 00:12:35,371
We are now departing…
[continues indistinctly]

315
00:12:35,438 --> 00:12:39,138
OFF WE GO TO THE MISSION CONTROL CENTER
THAT OVERSAW APOLLO 11'S MOON LANDING!

316
00:12:39,205 --> 00:12:41,705
[in Korean] Would you travel to space
if I bought you a ticket?

317
00:12:41,771 --> 00:12:42,938
- To space?
- Yes.

318
00:12:43,438 --> 00:12:44,638
For how long?

319
00:12:44,705 --> 00:12:45,871
HE NEEDS A SPECIFIC SCENARIO

320
00:12:45,938 --> 00:12:48,538
- How long are we talking about?
- About three days?

321
00:12:48,605 --> 00:12:49,838
- Three days?
- Yes.

322
00:12:50,571 --> 00:12:51,971
SHAKING HIS HEAD

323
00:12:52,038 --> 00:12:54,438
- Huh?
- Is it because space travel scares you?

324
00:12:54,505 --> 00:12:57,171
Space doesn't interest me all that much.

325
00:12:57,671 --> 00:13:00,305
- Does space not spark your interest?
- What?

326
00:13:00,371 --> 00:13:03,338
I'd rather you give me a ticket
to the US than to space.

327
00:13:03,405 --> 00:13:05,138
WANTS MORE OF THE US EVEN WHEN HE'S THERE

328
00:13:05,205 --> 00:13:07,138
- The US interests you more?
- Yes.

329
00:13:07,205 --> 00:13:09,171
- Send me to the US.
- [tour guide continues indistinctly]

330
00:13:09,238 --> 00:13:11,371
WHILE SEO-JIN PROFESSES HIS LOVE
FOR THE US FOR THE 100TH TIME

331
00:13:13,038 --> 00:13:15,938
THE MISSION CONTROL CENTER
SHOWS ITSELF JUST IN TIME

332
00:13:16,838 --> 00:13:18,271
CHRISTOPHER C. KRAFT JR.
MISSION CONTROL CENTER

333
00:13:18,338 --> 00:13:20,705
OVERSAW ALL MANNED MISSIONS
FROM APOLLO 11'S FIRST MOON LANDING

334
00:13:20,771 --> 00:13:22,371
TO THE INTERNATIONAL
SPACE STATION'S MISSIONS

335
00:13:22,938 --> 00:13:23,871
[Yung-suk] There's no window.

336
00:13:23,938 --> 00:13:25,405
THE PLACE YOU'VE SEEN IN COUNTLESS MOVIES

337
00:13:25,471 --> 00:13:26,305
[Dae-ju] You're right.

338
00:13:26,871 --> 00:13:28,138
There's the Mission Control Center.

339
00:13:28,205 --> 00:13:29,938
WHAT WILL THE HISTORIC
MISSION CONTROL ROOM LOOK LIKE?

340
00:13:30,005 --> 00:13:31,238
It's got a peculiar design.

341
00:13:31,305 --> 00:13:35,305
This building would've been around
since the 1960s, right?

342
00:13:35,371 --> 00:13:37,771
The new system is on the second floor,
and the old one is on the third.

343
00:13:37,838 --> 00:13:40,938
Doesn't it feel like the stairs
we take to go up to the studio?

344
00:13:41,005 --> 00:13:42,038
That's what I'm getting.

345
00:13:42,105 --> 00:13:43,171
CLIMBING SOMEWHAT FAMILIAR STAIRS

346
00:13:43,238 --> 00:13:46,238
- It's just an old building.
- Yes, it's really old.

347
00:13:46,805 --> 00:13:50,005
THEY'VE FINALLY REACHED
THE MISSION CONTROL CENTER!

348
00:13:50,538 --> 00:13:51,805
[Seo-jin] Oh.

349
00:13:51,871 --> 00:13:53,705
[Yung-suk] They handled
the moon landing here.

350
00:13:53,771 --> 00:13:55,805
[in English] "We have a problem, Houston."

351
00:13:55,871 --> 00:13:57,871
[in Korean] This is wild.

352
00:13:58,605 --> 00:14:01,538
I've seen things like this in movies.

353
00:14:01,605 --> 00:14:03,271
TOUR OF THE MISSION CONTROL ROOM BEGINS!

354
00:14:03,338 --> 00:14:05,771
[in English] <i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>
<i>my name is Gene Kranz.</i>

355
00:14:05,838 --> 00:14:12,071
<i>You're about to be transported back</i>
<i>to the afternoon of July 20th, 1969,</i>

356
00:14:12,138 --> 00:14:15,538
<i>as Apollo 11 astronauts</i>
<i>Neil Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin</i>

357
00:14:15,605 --> 00:14:17,971
<i>descended to the lunar surface.</i>

358
00:14:18,038 --> 00:14:21,205
<i>On that day,</i>
<i>my team was responsible for guiding…</i>

359
00:14:21,271 --> 00:14:22,671
EAGLE WAS APOLLO 11'S LUNAR LANDER

360
00:14:22,738 --> 00:14:25,005
<i>…Lunar Module "Eagle"</i>
<i>to a safe landing on the moon.</i>

361
00:14:25,071 --> 00:14:27,171
AT THAT MOMENT

362
00:14:27,238 --> 00:14:29,371
[Yung-suk in Korean] Oh. That's so cool.

363
00:14:29,438 --> 00:14:31,105
THEY START RE-ENACTING
THE EVENTS OF THAT HISTORIC DAY

364
00:14:31,671 --> 00:14:34,438
AS THE EAGLE GETS CLOSER
TO THE LUNAR SURFACE…

365
00:14:35,138 --> 00:14:39,338
THE CONTROL ROOM COMES ALIVE
IN A FLURRY OF ACTIVITY

366
00:14:39,905 --> 00:14:43,538
IMPRESSED

367
00:14:43,605 --> 00:14:45,338
THE CRITICAL MOMENT
OF HUMANITY'S FIRST MOON LANDING…

368
00:14:45,405 --> 00:14:47,071
[Seo-jin] Hey, there it is.

369
00:14:47,138 --> 00:14:48,805
[Yung-suk] Look at the TV screen.

370
00:14:48,871 --> 00:14:50,871
[man in English]
<i>Eagle, looking great. You're a go.</i>

371
00:14:50,938 --> 00:14:52,171
[lullaby plays]

372
00:14:52,238 --> 00:14:55,138
SEO-JIN SETS FOOT IN DREAMLAND

373
00:14:55,705 --> 00:14:59,005
THE CLOSER THE SPACECRAFT GETS TO THE MOON

374
00:14:59,905 --> 00:15:02,305
THE HEAVIER SEO-JIN'S EYELIDS GET…

375
00:15:02,938 --> 00:15:05,138
CHEWING

376
00:15:06,205 --> 00:15:10,605
THE EAGLE BEGINS ITS DESCENT

377
00:15:10,671 --> 00:15:15,005
Wait, to catch all that,
they would've needed a camera on the moon.

378
00:15:15,071 --> 00:15:17,138
Doesn't that mean that video is a fake?

379
00:15:17,205 --> 00:15:18,571
Could they have really filmed it?

380
00:15:18,638 --> 00:15:19,905
[Yung-suk] It must be fake.

381
00:15:19,971 --> 00:15:21,705
THE CAMERA WAS ALREADY ROLLING
BEFORE THE MOON LANDING

382
00:15:21,771 --> 00:15:23,705
That means they sent a team in advance.

383
00:15:24,605 --> 00:15:25,771
Who set up the camera there?

384
00:15:25,838 --> 00:15:28,038
They had it installed on the moon.

385
00:15:28,105 --> 00:15:31,038
SUGGESTING THE POSSIBILITY
OF ANOTHER LANDING PARTY

386
00:15:31,105 --> 00:15:33,271
- How did they film it?
- I think that's fake.

387
00:15:33,338 --> 00:15:35,738
YUNG-SUK AND DAE-JU ARE VERY INQUISITIVE

388
00:15:35,805 --> 00:15:37,338
They had a camera positioned there…

389
00:15:37,405 --> 00:15:39,005
It was already rolling when they landed.

390
00:15:39,071 --> 00:15:40,671
FASCINATED BY BOTH THE CONTENT
AND THE FILMING ITSELF

391
00:15:41,738 --> 00:15:42,871
[Yung-suk] Will we see him take a step?

392
00:15:42,938 --> 00:15:45,105
AND FINALLY…

393
00:15:45,705 --> 00:15:48,538
NEIL ARMSTRONG STARTS TO STEP DOWN
THE LADDER FROM THE EAGLE!

394
00:15:48,605 --> 00:15:50,171
EAGLE'S MOON LANDING
8:17 P.M., JULY 20, 1969

395
00:15:50,238 --> 00:15:51,838
HUMANITY'S MOON LANDING
2:56 A.M., JULY 21, 1969

396
00:15:52,571 --> 00:15:55,538
THIS HISTORIC LINE
WAS THEN BROADCAST TO THE WHOLE WORLD

397
00:15:55,605 --> 00:15:56,771
[Armstrong in English]

398
00:15:56,838 --> 00:15:58,671
<i>That's one small step for man,</i>

399
00:15:59,805 --> 00:16:02,071
<i>one giant leap for mankind.</i>

400
00:16:02,605 --> 00:16:04,605
- [in Korean] He must've prepared it.
- He said that right there…

401
00:16:04,671 --> 00:16:06,205
He had his line ready.

402
00:16:06,271 --> 00:16:07,838
JEALOUSY TOWARD ARMSTRONG'S ELOQUENCE

403
00:16:07,905 --> 00:16:09,571
[snoring softly]

404
00:16:11,338 --> 00:16:13,971
FINALLY CAUGHT THE NEWS
OF SEO-JIN'S DREAMLAND LANDING

405
00:16:14,038 --> 00:16:16,105
[indistinct announcement]

406
00:16:16,171 --> 00:16:18,071
CLOSE-UP REPORTING

407
00:16:18,905 --> 00:16:20,871
ALL CLEAR IN DREAMLAND LANDING

408
00:16:20,938 --> 00:16:22,005
[announce in English]

409
00:16:22,071 --> 00:16:24,105
<i>We thank you for visiting today.</i>

410
00:16:24,171 --> 00:16:26,905
[crowd clapping]

411
00:16:26,971 --> 00:16:30,205
CLAPPING IN TANDEM AS IF NOTHING HAPPENED

412
00:16:30,271 --> 00:16:32,671
[in Korean] Excuse me,
but if you were going to fall asleep--

413
00:16:32,738 --> 00:16:34,338
No way. I didn't miss a single word.

414
00:16:36,505 --> 00:16:39,105
YOUR OLD MAN'S NOT SLEEPING

415
00:16:39,171 --> 00:16:41,505
Besides, I've watched this many times.

416
00:16:41,571 --> 00:16:43,771
- You mean that video?
- It's suspicious.

417
00:16:43,838 --> 00:16:46,371
Did you see how the camera
was already installed on the moon?

418
00:16:46,438 --> 00:16:47,438
It was all set up.

419
00:16:47,505 --> 00:16:49,538
Someone had it installed
on the lunar surface.

420
00:16:49,605 --> 00:16:52,271
[Woo-jung] Maybe a satellite
that was already there filmed it?

421
00:16:52,338 --> 00:16:53,405
For sure.

422
00:16:53,905 --> 00:16:54,805
[Woo-jung] The lunar lander…

423
00:16:54,871 --> 00:16:57,071
To catch it all from the perfect angle?

424
00:16:57,138 --> 00:16:58,871
Try as you might,

425
00:16:58,938 --> 00:17:02,871
you couldn't have it located in the center
when the spacecraft could land anywhere.

426
00:17:02,938 --> 00:17:04,738
Are you suggesting the US pulled a con?

427
00:17:04,805 --> 00:17:07,471
Not exactly,
but the footage was rather questionable…

428
00:17:07,538 --> 00:17:09,205
[in English] What I'm saying is that…

429
00:17:09,271 --> 00:17:10,471
THESE TWO ARE VERY INQUISITIVE

430
00:17:10,538 --> 00:17:11,705
Come on, NASA.

431
00:17:11,771 --> 00:17:13,638
[Ye-seul in Korean]
Here we go. Three, two, one.

432
00:17:13,705 --> 00:17:16,371
SOUVENIR PHOTO
AT THE APOLLO MISSION CONTROL CENTER

433
00:17:17,638 --> 00:17:19,805
Who could've installed that camera?

434
00:17:19,871 --> 00:17:21,938
NEVER-ENDING SUSPICION

435
00:17:22,005 --> 00:17:24,604
- [indistinct announcement]
- It told a very dramatic story.

436
00:17:25,805 --> 00:17:27,471
Here's what I think.

437
00:17:28,305 --> 00:17:29,738
All tourists…

438
00:17:31,738 --> 00:17:33,038
are bound to get tired.

439
00:17:33,104 --> 00:17:35,771
- That's a pretty nice spot to rest.
- To take a nap?

440
00:17:35,838 --> 00:17:38,105
- The chairs were comfy.
- Because the chairs are comfortable.

441
00:17:38,171 --> 00:17:39,638
They dim the lights too.

442
00:17:39,705 --> 00:17:42,005
Yes, it's perfect for a deep sleep.

443
00:17:42,071 --> 00:17:43,871
- [Yung-suk] I get it.
- It can energize you.

444
00:17:43,938 --> 00:17:44,938
[Yung-suk] What a great idea.

445
00:17:45,005 --> 00:17:47,605
WHEN YOU'RE TIRED, RECHARGE YOURSELF
AT THE MISSION CONTROL CENTER

446
00:17:48,338 --> 00:17:51,638
NOW THAT THEY'VE RECOVERED,
THEY CAN GO TO THE NEXT STOP!

447
00:17:53,005 --> 00:17:55,005
They must train the astronauts
in this mock-up set.

448
00:17:55,071 --> 00:17:57,171
They've created a set here.

449
00:17:58,471 --> 00:17:59,305
Oh!

450
00:17:59,371 --> 00:18:00,538
IN ADMIRATION

451
00:18:00,605 --> 00:18:03,038
This is the ISS.

452
00:18:07,538 --> 00:18:09,671
MOCK-UPS OF THE ISS
AND NEXT-GENERATION SPACECRAFTS

453
00:18:09,738 --> 00:18:12,005
PREPARED TO TRAIN THE NEW ASTRONAUTS

454
00:18:12,071 --> 00:18:14,471
ASTRONAUTS PREPARE THEMSELVES
FOR A MISSION IN SPACE

455
00:18:14,538 --> 00:18:16,971
WHILE ENGINEERS DESIGN
AND ENHANCE SPACECRAFT EQUIPMENT

456
00:18:17,038 --> 00:18:19,338
Isn't this a mock-up of the ISS?

457
00:18:19,405 --> 00:18:20,238
THAT'S CORRECT

458
00:18:20,305 --> 00:18:22,571
That's how it looked on news clips.

459
00:18:22,638 --> 00:18:25,305
They must've created a full-scale model

460
00:18:25,371 --> 00:18:28,105
to provide a training area
for the personnel.

461
00:18:28,171 --> 00:18:30,271
They have this gigantic structure
floating in space?

462
00:18:30,338 --> 00:18:31,971
SIMPLY AMAZED

463
00:18:32,038 --> 00:18:34,171
I don't think they have training today.

464
00:18:34,238 --> 00:18:37,138
- I almost misread that as "Zara."
- [Woo-jung laughs]

465
00:18:37,205 --> 00:18:39,405
- [chuckles]
- [Yung-suk] What, "Zarya"?

466
00:18:39,471 --> 00:18:41,871
THE RUSSIAN-MADE ZARYA MODULE
IS THE HISTORIC FIRST MODULE OF THE ISS

467
00:18:41,938 --> 00:18:44,071
SYMBOLIZING THE BEGINNING
OF INTERNATIONAL COOPERATION

468
00:18:44,871 --> 00:18:46,638
[Seo-jin] Remove the y,
and you get "Zara."

469
00:18:46,705 --> 00:18:49,038
SHOPPING IS ALL HE THINKS ABOUT

470
00:18:50,005 --> 00:18:51,638
There are people down there.

471
00:18:51,705 --> 00:18:53,471
- They must do actual training here.
- [Yung-suk] Yes.

472
00:18:53,538 --> 00:18:54,938
They must really train people here.

473
00:18:55,005 --> 00:18:58,871
NASA EMPLOYEES ON DUTY SPOTTED!

474
00:18:58,938 --> 00:19:00,538
[man in English]

475
00:19:00,605 --> 00:19:03,771
<i>also known</i>
<i>as the Astronaut Training Facility.</i>

476
00:19:03,838 --> 00:19:06,405
<i>This building houses</i>
<i>mock-ups and models of spacecraft,</i>

477
00:19:06,471 --> 00:19:08,205
<i>robots, and training simulators.</i>

478
00:19:08,271 --> 00:19:09,605
<i>And since 1980,</i>

479
00:19:09,671 --> 00:19:12,338
<i>every NASA astronaut</i>
<i>has walked the floors of this building</i>

480
00:19:12,405 --> 00:19:14,571
<i>in preparation for their next mission.</i>

481
00:19:14,638 --> 00:19:17,738
<i>And since 1980,</i>
<i>every NASA astronaut has walked…</i>

482
00:19:17,805 --> 00:19:19,905
[in Korean] Don't they all
look like actors?

483
00:19:20,771 --> 00:19:22,438
- Actors.
- They look like paid actors.

484
00:19:22,971 --> 00:19:26,171
It seems you've lost faith altogether.

485
00:19:26,238 --> 00:19:27,971
They just look like hired actors.

486
00:19:28,038 --> 00:19:30,571
ENDLESS CONSPIRACY THEORIES
FROM THE DIRECTOR-WRITER DUO

487
00:19:30,638 --> 00:19:32,371
[Seo-jin]
Are you suggesting they're saying,

488
00:19:32,438 --> 00:19:33,705
"Guys, don't look up."

489
00:19:33,771 --> 00:19:36,071
"Just stay in the group."

490
00:19:36,138 --> 00:19:37,771
FLABBERGASTED

491
00:19:37,838 --> 00:19:40,038
- [Yung-suk] "They're taking photos."
- [Dae-ju] "Let's get in formation."

492
00:19:40,105 --> 00:19:41,471
[Yung-suk]
"What are we having for dinner?"

493
00:19:41,538 --> 00:19:43,705
"Four plus two equals seven."

494
00:19:43,771 --> 00:19:45,905
- My doubt is growing.
- [Dae-ju] "Where did you get that shirt?"

495
00:19:45,971 --> 00:19:46,805
THEY'RE JUST JOKING

496
00:19:47,371 --> 00:19:50,738
- Do you believe aliens exist, Yung-suk?
- Aliens? Sure.

497
00:19:50,805 --> 00:19:52,071
I believe they exist too.

498
00:19:52,138 --> 00:19:53,871
How could they not
when the space is so vast?

499
00:19:53,938 --> 00:19:56,005
You question the moon landing
but believe in aliens?

500
00:19:56,571 --> 00:19:59,138
[Yung-suk] The people here
must have amazing job satisfaction.

501
00:19:59,205 --> 00:20:02,938
[Ye-seul] But they'll have tourists
coming in every hour and watching them.

502
00:20:03,005 --> 00:20:05,505
Can you edit the footage here, Ye-seul?

503
00:20:05,571 --> 00:20:07,838
You'd have us discussing your duties too.

504
00:20:07,905 --> 00:20:11,971
"Director Kim Ye-seul here
is working on <i>Ready or Not: Texas."</i>

505
00:20:12,471 --> 00:20:14,305
[Ye-seul] That might be rough.

506
00:20:14,371 --> 00:20:16,938
"Why don't we give Director Kim a wave?"

507
00:20:17,005 --> 00:20:19,605
SEEING IT FROM THEIR PERSPECTIVE,
THE NASA WORK ENVIRONMENT IS TERRIFYING

508
00:20:19,671 --> 00:20:22,771
THEIR FINAL STOP IS THE VR EXPERIENCE

509
00:20:22,838 --> 00:20:24,638
ALL ABOARD THE VIRTUAL SPACECRAFT

510
00:20:24,705 --> 00:20:27,105
[Woo-jung] Return home safely.

511
00:20:28,271 --> 00:20:30,071
AS ORDERED BY COMMANDER WOO-JUNG

512
00:20:30,138 --> 00:20:31,071
THE SPACECRAFT DEPARTS

513
00:20:31,138 --> 00:20:32,471
[Yung-suk] Oh! My gosh, Seo-jin.

514
00:20:32,538 --> 00:20:33,938
Oh, man. This is scary.

515
00:20:34,005 --> 00:20:35,538
Oh, shoot.

516
00:20:35,605 --> 00:20:37,071
This is terrifying.

517
00:20:37,871 --> 00:20:39,438
WAY TOO INTO THE EXPERIENCE

518
00:20:40,438 --> 00:20:42,305
DISTANCE BETWEEN THE EARTH
AND THE SPACECRAFT GROWS

519
00:20:42,371 --> 00:20:43,838
[Yung-suk] See you.

520
00:20:44,738 --> 00:20:46,238
Whoa.

521
00:20:46,305 --> 00:20:49,405
- Hey, this is the best.
- [laughs, whoops]

522
00:20:49,471 --> 00:20:50,938
EXCITED CHEER

523
00:20:51,005 --> 00:20:53,805
[Woo-jung] He's the loudest.
Even the children are quiet.

524
00:20:55,271 --> 00:20:58,071
THEIR DESTINATION, THE MOON, APPEARS

525
00:20:58,138 --> 00:21:00,438
We're about to land.

526
00:21:00,971 --> 00:21:03,205
- Whoa.
- There we go.

527
00:21:03,271 --> 00:21:04,171
MOON LANDING MISSION ACCOMPLISHED

528
00:21:04,238 --> 00:21:06,005
[Dae-ju] Whoa. Whoa!

529
00:21:06,071 --> 00:21:08,805
THEY'VE FINALLY REACHED THE MOON

530
00:21:13,871 --> 00:21:15,871
This is what it would've felt like.

531
00:21:15,938 --> 00:21:19,471
AFTER THE DREAMY TRIP TO THE MOON…

532
00:21:20,238 --> 00:21:21,305
That was fun.

533
00:21:21,371 --> 00:21:22,671
BACK TO EARTH

534
00:21:22,738 --> 00:21:24,838
I can sum this up in a single sentence.

535
00:21:24,905 --> 00:21:26,371
It's awesome.

536
00:21:26,438 --> 00:21:27,271
PROUD

537
00:21:27,338 --> 00:21:28,171
Did you not try this?

538
00:21:28,738 --> 00:21:31,971
Out of everything we've tried
in the center, this is the best.

539
00:21:32,038 --> 00:21:33,938
- [Dae-ju] This is by far the best.
- Really?

540
00:21:34,005 --> 00:21:35,905
This is the ultimate experience.

541
00:21:35,971 --> 00:21:37,005
I told you, didn't I?

542
00:21:37,071 --> 00:21:39,705
- Apollo 11 did land on the moon.
- [Woo-jung] You think so?

543
00:21:39,771 --> 00:21:42,205
I get it now. I'm finally convinced.

544
00:21:42,271 --> 00:21:45,171
There's no way it didn't land on the moon.

545
00:21:45,238 --> 00:21:46,771
<i>Yes, it got there.</i>

546
00:21:46,838 --> 00:21:49,438
<i>Apollo 11 succeeded</i>
<i>in its moon landing mission.</i>

547
00:21:49,505 --> 00:21:50,838
<i>It had a huge success for sure.</i>

548
00:21:52,038 --> 00:21:54,538
NEXT MORNING IN HOUSTON

549
00:21:54,605 --> 00:21:56,538
I get where we are, Seo-jin.

550
00:21:56,605 --> 00:21:58,271
Just one block into this neighborhood,

551
00:21:59,205 --> 00:22:01,305
[Seo-jin] I see signs saying "golden"
and "dim sum" everywhere.

552
00:22:01,371 --> 00:22:02,871
It's packed with everything I love.

553
00:22:02,938 --> 00:22:04,371
LAST EVENING

554
00:22:04,438 --> 00:22:06,705
Why don't we get some dim sum? [chuckles]

555
00:22:06,771 --> 00:22:07,905
SUGGESTING HIS FAVORITE DISH

556
00:22:07,971 --> 00:22:09,871
We could hit Chinatown for some dim sum.

557
00:22:09,938 --> 00:22:13,005
Hey, tomorrow lunch, dim sum, man.

558
00:22:13,071 --> 00:22:14,971
- Eleven o'clock, brunch.
- [in Korean] For brunch…

559
00:22:15,038 --> 00:22:17,005
- Let's have some dim sum for brunch.
- Oh, yeah.

560
00:22:17,071 --> 00:22:18,805
[in Korean] Oh. The whole neighborhood is…

561
00:22:18,871 --> 00:22:20,171
Hey, I guess we're in Hong Kong.

562
00:22:20,238 --> 00:22:22,971
[Woo-jung] Doesn't that look like
a palace? It's an actual palace.

563
00:22:23,505 --> 00:22:26,105
- [Seo-jin] It's a Hong Kong castle.
- [Yung-suk] Tell me about it.

564
00:22:26,771 --> 00:22:28,805
- [Woo-jung] It's a surprise encounter.
- [Yung-suk] We stumbled into Hong Kong.

565
00:22:28,871 --> 00:22:30,571
[Woo-jung] <i>Ready or Not: Hong Kong.</i>

566
00:22:30,638 --> 00:22:32,671
[Seo-jin] I see some water over there.

567
00:22:32,738 --> 00:22:35,038
- They built a pond.
- [men laugh]

568
00:22:35,105 --> 00:22:36,371
[Dae-ju] That's one huge restaurant.

569
00:22:36,438 --> 00:22:39,138
WATCH CLOSELY TO SEE IF THEIR DIM SUM
CAN WIN OVER SEO-JIN'S HEART

570
00:22:39,205 --> 00:22:41,238
ENTERING THE RESTAURANT

571
00:22:41,305 --> 00:22:44,138
[vocalizes excitedly] Ah.
I see loads of familiar round tables.

572
00:22:44,738 --> 00:22:46,638
[in English] I'm waiting for a cart.

573
00:22:46,705 --> 00:22:48,138
The dim sum cart.

574
00:22:49,571 --> 00:22:51,071
[in Korean] I guess
the cart will come this way.

575
00:22:51,138 --> 00:22:54,105
THE DIM SUM CARTS
COME TO YOUR TABLE WHILE YOU SIT

576
00:22:54,171 --> 00:22:56,571
We won't need to read the menu.

577
00:22:56,638 --> 00:22:59,338
What I love about dim sum restaurants is…

578
00:22:59,405 --> 00:23:00,671
Here she comes.

579
00:23:00,738 --> 00:23:02,705
- You don't need to choose…
- Just pick up steamers.

580
00:23:02,771 --> 00:23:03,705
[Yung-suk] Grab them.

581
00:23:03,771 --> 00:23:05,671
ONCE THE CART COMES,
PICK WHATEVER LOOKS GOOD

582
00:23:05,738 --> 00:23:08,038
- [Seo-jin] Pick up whatever.
- [Yung-suk] We want two steamers each.

583
00:23:08,105 --> 00:23:10,471
ORDERED 2 STEAMERS OF EACH

584
00:23:10,538 --> 00:23:11,371
Okay.

585
00:23:12,405 --> 00:23:14,571
We've got to try every dish here.

586
00:23:14,638 --> 00:23:16,271
That looks great.

587
00:23:16,338 --> 00:23:18,705
SHUMAI: A DUMPLING STEAMED
WITH THE WRAPPER LEFT OPEN ON TOP

588
00:23:18,771 --> 00:23:21,738
[Dae-ju] She's stamping the items
we picked to keep track.

589
00:23:21,805 --> 00:23:23,371
DISH COUNT MARKED WITH A STAMP!

590
00:23:23,438 --> 00:23:26,238
Shouldn't we mix the condiments
in the perfect ratio?

591
00:23:27,205 --> 00:23:29,205
They have this ready-made sauce.

592
00:23:29,271 --> 00:23:30,538
[Woo-jung] I'm getting bits of everything.

593
00:23:30,605 --> 00:23:31,905
- Hello.
- Rice noodle rolls?

594
00:23:31,971 --> 00:23:33,605
- Rice noodle rolls?
- Rice noodle rolls.

595
00:23:33,671 --> 00:23:35,171
- [in English] You want one?
- Yes.

596
00:23:35,238 --> 00:23:36,938
LEGION OF DIM SUM APPEARS NONSTOP

597
00:23:37,005 --> 00:23:38,605
THIN-SKINNED DIM SUM WITH SOY-BASED SAUCE

598
00:23:38,671 --> 00:23:40,971
- [Yung-suk in Korean] Is this shrimp?
- [Seo-jin] That's shrimp. I mean this one.

599
00:23:41,038 --> 00:23:43,371
- [woman] Barbecue.
- [Seo-jin] Okay, so this is pork.

600
00:23:44,238 --> 00:23:46,871
BEEF RICE NOODLE ROLLS

601
00:23:47,605 --> 00:23:48,438
Two.

602
00:23:48,505 --> 00:23:49,805
ORDERING AND MIXING SAUCE AT THE SAME TIME

603
00:23:49,871 --> 00:23:51,105
- Thank you.
- [woman] Thank you.

604
00:23:51,171 --> 00:23:53,005
AFTER ORDERING A WHOLE LOT OF DISHES

605
00:23:54,138 --> 00:23:58,405
To begin with,
I added a touch of spicy chili oil.

606
00:23:58,471 --> 00:24:02,238
Following Seo-jin's recipe,
I'm going to add some sriracha sauce.

607
00:24:02,305 --> 00:24:04,505
BIG BITE

608
00:24:04,571 --> 00:24:06,138
It all comes down to personal taste.

609
00:24:06,205 --> 00:24:07,805
SEO-JIN WOLFS DOWN FOOD QUIETLY

610
00:24:08,705 --> 00:24:10,938
APPRECIATIVE SQUEALS

611
00:24:11,671 --> 00:24:14,371
THE OVER-THE-TOP YOUTUBER

612
00:24:14,438 --> 00:24:16,338
ENTHUSIASTIC GROAN

613
00:24:16,405 --> 00:24:17,905
Hey, it's good.

614
00:24:17,971 --> 00:24:19,805
- [Woo-jung] Is that good, Yung-suk?
- Mm!

615
00:24:19,871 --> 00:24:21,038
[Woo-jung] This is the best fast food.

616
00:24:21,105 --> 00:24:22,171
MUKBANG YOUTUBER CERTIFIED

617
00:24:22,238 --> 00:24:24,338
Here comes another cart.
Should we pick some more?

618
00:24:24,405 --> 00:24:25,671
ANOTHER DIM SUM CART APPROACHES

619
00:24:25,738 --> 00:24:27,738
- Let's get that one only.
- Just this one?

620
00:24:27,805 --> 00:24:29,271
ORDERING AGAIN

621
00:24:29,338 --> 00:24:31,605
[Yung-suk] I want to review that too.
Please pass me one.

622
00:24:31,671 --> 00:24:32,605
[Woo-jung] Sure, try it.

623
00:24:33,838 --> 00:24:35,238
Care to comment?

624
00:24:35,305 --> 00:24:36,605
TAKEN ABACK

625
00:24:36,671 --> 00:24:37,705
Go ahead and do it.

626
00:24:37,771 --> 00:24:39,438
- Do your thing.
- What do you mean?

627
00:24:39,505 --> 00:24:42,338
- Review the dish.
- This isn't a one-man job, you know.

628
00:24:42,405 --> 00:24:44,205
TRIES IT ANYWAY

629
00:24:44,271 --> 00:24:45,405
Does it have pork filling?

630
00:24:45,471 --> 00:24:46,738
It's not odd at all, but…

631
00:24:49,105 --> 00:24:51,671
What do you think is inside, Ye-seul?
Ground pork?

632
00:24:51,738 --> 00:24:54,271
[Ye-seul] I think it has
ground pork inside.

633
00:24:54,338 --> 00:24:55,805
It's pretty good.

634
00:24:55,871 --> 00:24:57,271
- Yes, it's good.
- It's good.

635
00:24:57,338 --> 00:24:59,138
[Woo-jung] It's a bit like
the Korean meatball.

636
00:24:59,205 --> 00:25:00,538
[Dae-ju] Yes, that's right.

637
00:25:00,605 --> 00:25:03,171
[Woo-jung] I've always wondered
where this sriracha brand is from.

638
00:25:03,238 --> 00:25:05,371
- The US.
- [Woo-jung] Really?

639
00:25:05,438 --> 00:25:06,438
"Everything's American."

640
00:25:06,505 --> 00:25:08,171
- [Woo-jung] Isn't it a Chinese brand?
- It's American.

641
00:25:08,238 --> 00:25:11,638
Here's Seo-jin presenting his case
that everything originates from the US.

642
00:25:11,705 --> 00:25:14,638
[Ye-seul] Most people here
seem to be locals.

643
00:25:14,705 --> 00:25:17,338
This must be the locals' favorite spot.

644
00:25:17,405 --> 00:25:19,105
- [Yung-suk] It sure looks that way.
- [Ye-seul] For sure.

645
00:25:19,171 --> 00:25:20,838
It's the weekend.

646
00:25:20,905 --> 00:25:23,871
They must have a routine
like eating out after the church service.

647
00:25:23,938 --> 00:25:25,271
Who goes to church on a Saturday?

648
00:25:25,338 --> 00:25:26,338
Don't they go to church?

649
00:25:26,405 --> 00:25:29,105
For your information,
church services are held on Sundays.

650
00:25:29,171 --> 00:25:30,138
Is it Saturday today?

651
00:25:30,205 --> 00:25:31,471
CHURCH SERVICES ARE ON SUNDAY,
AND TODAY'S SATURDAY

652
00:25:31,538 --> 00:25:34,005
Americans go to church on Sundays too.
Who goes to church on a Saturday?

653
00:25:34,071 --> 00:25:37,605
[Woo-jung] Why are you nitpicking?
He only meant to say it's the weekend.

654
00:25:37,671 --> 00:25:40,305
We should correct the wrong information
right then and there.

655
00:25:40,371 --> 00:25:42,071
- Good job.
- [Seo-jin] What?

656
00:25:42,138 --> 00:25:44,238
At long last,
he's not licking his fingers.

657
00:25:44,838 --> 00:25:46,738
YUNG-SUK USES HIS HANDS TO EAT
MORE OFTEN THAN OTHER ADULTS

658
00:25:46,805 --> 00:25:48,305
- Huh?
- It's because he's got chopsticks now.

659
00:25:48,371 --> 00:25:50,838
- [in English] These chopsticks.
- [in Korean] He's always had some.

660
00:25:52,871 --> 00:25:54,771
These have chives inside.

661
00:25:54,838 --> 00:25:56,371
[Yung-suk] They make them this big?

662
00:25:56,438 --> 00:25:57,505
CHIVE DUMPLINGS

663
00:25:57,571 --> 00:25:58,538
These are huge.

664
00:25:58,605 --> 00:26:02,071
This looks twice the size of the others.

665
00:26:03,938 --> 00:26:06,338
[Dae-ju] You're really quick
to use your hands.

666
00:26:06,405 --> 00:26:09,005
He's ended up using his hands again.

667
00:26:09,071 --> 00:26:10,138
It's twice as large.

668
00:26:10,205 --> 00:26:11,305
HIS HANDS COULDN'T RESIST

669
00:26:11,371 --> 00:26:12,638
[Dae-ju] His hands are his go-to tool.

670
00:26:12,705 --> 00:26:15,305
- I was hoping he wouldn't.
- This is how you eat stuff like this.

671
00:26:16,205 --> 00:26:18,905
YUNG-SUK WASHED HIS HANDS BEFORE THE MEAL

672
00:26:19,605 --> 00:26:20,505
NEXT UP IS XIAOLONGBAO

673
00:26:20,571 --> 00:26:22,471
[Woo-jung] I want your rating
on this, Seo-jin.

674
00:26:22,538 --> 00:26:24,538
The dish that makes or breaks
a dim sum restaurant

675
00:26:24,605 --> 00:26:26,538
- is <i>xiaolongbao.</i>
- [Woo-jung] Tell me about it.

676
00:26:26,605 --> 00:26:30,438
In the end,
it's all about their <i>xiaolongbao.</i>

677
00:26:30,505 --> 00:26:32,505
They served it in this little foil cup.

678
00:26:32,571 --> 00:26:34,205
USING HIS HAND AGAIN
AS IF HE CAN'T SENSE THE HEAT

679
00:26:34,271 --> 00:26:37,438
Be careful.
This can scald your mouth and tongue.

680
00:26:37,505 --> 00:26:40,971
- I just picked it up and put it back down.
- [all laughing]

681
00:26:41,038 --> 00:26:44,838
Take the whole thing in one bite,
and you'll burn your mouth.

682
00:26:46,305 --> 00:26:48,571
We're supposed to place it in a spoon.

683
00:26:48,638 --> 00:26:50,405
I think they gave us the foil cup instead.

684
00:26:50,471 --> 00:26:53,271
It's too hot at the moment,
so I'll put it in here.

685
00:26:53,338 --> 00:26:55,938
IF YOU DON'T HAVE A SPOON,
USE A CUP AND CUT IT OPEN TO COOL

686
00:26:56,005 --> 00:26:57,905
[Woo-jung] Did you pour
the jasmine tea into it?

687
00:26:57,971 --> 00:27:01,071
- No, it was empty.
- He's using the cup as a container.

688
00:27:01,138 --> 00:27:04,205
I've got no choice.
The juice is way too hot.

689
00:27:04,271 --> 00:27:05,505
BLOWING ON THE DUMPLING

690
00:27:05,571 --> 00:27:07,305
It's supposed to scald your mouth.

691
00:27:09,005 --> 00:27:10,671
JEERING

692
00:27:10,738 --> 00:27:12,438
You can't get the full flavor this way.

693
00:27:12,505 --> 00:27:14,271
This isn't my idea of proper <i>xiaolongbao.</i>

694
00:27:14,338 --> 00:27:16,638
Many think it's okay to have
the soup and the filling separate.

695
00:27:16,705 --> 00:27:17,805
Let's see you eat it.

696
00:27:17,871 --> 00:27:18,905
As for me…

697
00:27:18,971 --> 00:27:21,005
- Aren't you supposed to eat it whole?
- So do it.

698
00:27:21,071 --> 00:27:22,071
PICKS IT UP WITH HIS HAND

699
00:27:22,138 --> 00:27:24,238
That's the correct way. So do it.

700
00:27:24,305 --> 00:27:25,371
[Dae-ju] Puncture it first.

701
00:27:25,438 --> 00:27:27,905
- It's way too hot.
- [all laugh]

702
00:27:27,971 --> 00:27:30,338
Where did they cook this?
It's still this hot.

703
00:27:30,405 --> 00:27:31,705
MOST DIM SUM DISHES
ARE PREPARED IN A STEAMER

704
00:27:31,771 --> 00:27:33,971
They don't have much variety here.

705
00:27:34,471 --> 00:27:36,571
- There are so many here.
- [Woo-jung] The menu has a long list.

706
00:27:36,638 --> 00:27:39,271
- Do we need to order them?
- Place an order, then.

707
00:27:40,038 --> 00:27:42,205
- [Woo-jung] Is there anything you'd like?
- [Ye-seul] Well…

708
00:27:42,271 --> 00:27:46,171
I want those crispy BBQ buns…

709
00:27:46,238 --> 00:27:48,005
What are they called again?
I can't recall.

710
00:27:48,071 --> 00:27:50,338
I can't recall the name either.
Can you find it there?

711
00:27:50,405 --> 00:27:53,105
PROCEEDS TO CHECK THE MENU HIMSELF

712
00:27:54,405 --> 00:27:56,371
I'm sorry, but I can't read a thing.

713
00:27:57,938 --> 00:27:59,205
[Woo-jung] You can't read this?

714
00:27:59,271 --> 00:28:00,605
- [Yung-suk] Decoding failed.
- [Ye-seul] Oh, dear.

715
00:28:00,671 --> 00:28:03,005
- [Yung-suk] "I'm sorry, but I can't read."
- [Ye-seul] "I can't read a thing."

716
00:28:03,071 --> 00:28:04,505
SETBACK DUE TO AGE-RELATED FARSIGHTEDNESS

717
00:28:05,371 --> 00:28:09,438
- "I'm sorry, but I can't read a thing."
- [Ye-seul] That was his first apology.

718
00:28:09,505 --> 00:28:12,205
I forgot to take lutein in the morning,
and that's affecting my sight.

719
00:28:14,505 --> 00:28:15,871
TAKING OUT HIS GLASSES

720
00:28:15,938 --> 00:28:19,171
- Pass me the menu again.
- [all laughing]

721
00:28:19,238 --> 00:28:20,638
EYEBROWS MOVING UP AND DOWN

722
00:28:20,705 --> 00:28:21,671
Let me have it.

723
00:28:21,738 --> 00:28:22,971
ITEM EQUIPPED

724
00:28:23,038 --> 00:28:24,338
STUDYING THE MENU WITH A SCHOLARLY LOOK

725
00:28:24,405 --> 00:28:25,638
- [Yung-suk] Seriously…
- [Yu-jin] It's hilarious.

726
00:28:25,705 --> 00:28:26,871
Seo-jin.

727
00:28:26,938 --> 00:28:29,138
You're the true adult of our generation.

728
00:28:29,205 --> 00:28:30,438
WORTHY ROLE MODEL

729
00:28:30,505 --> 00:28:33,771
- A truly responsible adult.
- [Yu-jin] He put aside his pride…

730
00:28:33,838 --> 00:28:36,238
- My gosh, Yu-jin.
- …to get food for his younger colleagues.

731
00:28:36,805 --> 00:28:38,205
I made an effort.

732
00:28:38,705 --> 00:28:40,338
[Yu-jin] We scored a great line today.

733
00:28:40,405 --> 00:28:41,871
"I'm sorry. I can't see."

734
00:28:41,938 --> 00:28:44,705
It's your personal best
since "Does it hurt? It hurts me too."

735
00:28:44,771 --> 00:28:46,538
A MEMORABLE LINE
FROM THE DIM SUM RESTAURANT

736
00:28:46,605 --> 00:28:48,338
DELIGHTED

737
00:28:48,405 --> 00:28:51,905
What do you say to playing
the middle-aged lead in a romance series?

738
00:28:51,971 --> 00:28:52,871
Titled <i>I'm Sorry, I Can't See?</i>

739
00:28:52,938 --> 00:28:54,905
[Yu-jin] I can see myself crying
while writing it.

740
00:28:54,971 --> 00:28:56,538
The leads are in a European restaurant.

741
00:28:56,605 --> 00:28:58,105
The female lead finds a note saying,

742
00:28:58,171 --> 00:29:00,571
"I'm sorry, I can't see,"
when she returns from the restroom.

743
00:29:00,638 --> 00:29:02,005
The guy then disappears.

744
00:29:02,071 --> 00:29:05,371
She later finds him,
living all alone deep in the mountains.

745
00:29:05,438 --> 00:29:09,371
By that point, the man
had gone completely blind. [laughing]

746
00:29:09,438 --> 00:29:11,605
She came all the way to find him,
but he can't see her.

747
00:29:11,671 --> 00:29:13,038
TAKE GOOD CARE OF YOUR EYES

748
00:29:13,105 --> 00:29:15,505
All the years he lived in the mountains…

749
00:29:15,571 --> 00:29:19,071
[Woo-jung] If you were offered a role,
would you star in a romance series?

750
00:29:20,071 --> 00:29:22,171
Perhaps in a nursing home.

751
00:29:23,005 --> 00:29:26,205
[Woo-jung] Middle-aged romance
seems like it would be so different.

752
00:29:26,271 --> 00:29:28,005
It's not like romance in your twenties.

753
00:29:28,071 --> 00:29:29,438
The love will feel just as strong.

754
00:29:29,505 --> 00:29:32,905
When I was in my twenties,
my father was in his fifties.

755
00:29:33,438 --> 00:29:36,071
I wondered what he finds joy in.

756
00:29:36,138 --> 00:29:37,805
[Woo-jung] You understand him
completely now, right?

757
00:29:37,871 --> 00:29:41,338
I used to wonder what fun there was,
but I'm living just the same now.

758
00:29:41,405 --> 00:29:42,771
HOLLOW CHUCKLE

759
00:29:42,838 --> 00:29:45,005
- There's always something new to enjoy.
- [Woo-jung] You're right.

760
00:29:45,071 --> 00:29:46,371
[Yung-suk]
There's always a reason to live.

761
00:29:46,438 --> 00:29:48,838
- Every stage of life has its own joy.
- [Woo-jung] Absolutely.

762
00:29:48,905 --> 00:29:50,171
Let's go. We have our material.

763
00:29:50,238 --> 00:29:51,838
Let's decide on our next stop first.

764
00:29:51,905 --> 00:29:53,305
Right, we haven't
decided that yet. [laughs]

765
00:29:53,371 --> 00:29:54,705
TALE OF THE AIMLESS TRAVELERS
TO BE CONTINUED…

766
00:29:54,771 --> 00:29:56,771
[country music playing]

767
00:30:43,471 --> 00:30:45,471
Subtitle translation by: Jeongwoo Kim
